# OKay Language Code of Conduct

Welcome to the OKay Language community! We are committed to providing a safe and inclusive environment for everyone involved in our project, including contributors, maintainers, and users. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for behavior and sets the foundation for a positive and respectful community.

## Our Pledge

In the interest of fostering an open and welcoming community, we, as contributors and maintainers, pledge to:

- Be respectful and inclusive towards all individuals, regardless of their backgrounds, identities, or experiences.
- Create an environment where everyone feels safe to express their opinions and ideas.
- Be empathetic and understanding towards differing viewpoints and experiences.
- Address any conflicts or issues that arise with sensitivity and respect.

## Expected Behavior

To contribute to a healthy and collaborative community, we expect all participants to:

- Be considerate, respectful, and kind in all interactions.
- Use inclusive language and avoid any form of offensive, discriminatory, or harassing language or behavior.
- Respect differing opinions and perspectives.
- Be open to constructive feedback and provide it in a constructive manner.
- Strive to collaborate and work towards the best interests of the community and project.

## Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are considered unacceptable and will not be tolerated within our community:

- Harassment, discrimination, or any form of offensive behavior towards any individual or group.
- Intimidation, bullying, or personal attacks.
- Trolling, flaming, or derogatory comments, whether in public or private communication channels.
- Spamming, solicitation, or unauthorized advertising.
- Any other conduct that could reasonably be considered inappropriate within a professional setting.

## Reporting and Enforcement

If you encounter any violations of this Code of Conduct or have concerns regarding inappropriate behavior, please report the issue by contacting [contact person or team] at [contact email]. All reports will be kept confidential and will be reviewed and addressed promptly. We reserve the right to take appropriate action, including warning, temporary or permanent bans, and reporting to relevant authorities, as deemed necessary.

## Attribution

This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant (https://www.contributor-covenant.org), version 2.0, and the Open Source Guide's "Creating a Code of Conduct" template.

## Let's Build an Amazing Community!

By participating in the OKay Language community, you agree to abide by this Code of Conduct. Together, let's create a welcoming and inclusive space where everyone can collaborate, learn, and contribute to the growth and success of the project.

We appreciate your cooperation and look forward to a positive and enriching experience!

